    <p>Ex­plor­ing South­east Asia: A Jour­ney Through Art And Time</p>
    <p>This cu­rated show­case from the Nanyang Academy of Fine Arts’ (Nafa) per­ma­nent col­lec­tion of­fers a glimpse of the art prac­tices and cul­tural hall­marks of the re­gion as in­ter­preted by artists in Sin­ga­pore, Malaysia and Thai­land. The ex­hib­ited works span from 1949 to last year and are grouped by themes.</p>
    <p>The Ngee Ann Kongsi Gal­leries 1 & 2, Nafa Cam­pus 1, 80 Ben­coolen Street</p>
    <p>City Hall/Bugis</p>
    <p>Till Oct 25, 11am - 7pm</p>
    <p>(closed on Mon)</p>
    <p>Free</p>
    <p>E-mail art­gal­leries@nafa.edu.sg</p>


